Finland had a balance of trade surplus of 2,943  million marks (about 545 million dollars) in April, according to official  figures released here Wednesday.
The Government Bureau of Customs said exports last month amounted to  12,341 million marks (about 2,285 million dollars) and imports to 9,398  million marks (about 1,740 million dollars).
For the first four months of the year, Finland had a trade surplus of  12,746 million marks (about 2,360 million dollars) compared with a surplus of  7,044 million marks (about 1,304 million dollars) for the corresponding period  last year.
In April last year exports were 11,432 million marks (about 2,117 million  dollars) and imports 9,665 million marks (about 1,790 million dollars).
